1
00:00:06,500 --> 00:00:09,750
(People say life is unpredictable.)

2
00:00:11,030 --> 00:00:12,300
(Who would have thought?)

3
00:00:12,610 --> 00:00:14,990
(The naive country girl, Giselle,)

4
00:00:16,880 --> 00:00:21,150
would fall in love, be betrayed,
and then...

5
00:00:22,340 --> 00:00:25,500
go crazy.

6
00:00:52,260 --> 00:00:53,880
(Just like how I didn't know)

7
00:00:54,500 --> 00:00:55,640
(I would meet you,)

8
00:00:56,880 --> 00:00:59,160
(find you, and fall in love with you.)

9
00:01:00,880 --> 00:01:02,110
(Just like)

10
00:01:02,990 --> 00:01:05,019
(how we don't know
what our ending would be.)

11
00:02:38,650 --> 00:02:39,829
Great job, really.

12
00:02:44,060 --> 00:02:45,820
It took me a long time.

13
00:02:48,720 --> 00:02:49,820
I was

14
00:02:51,890 --> 00:02:53,430
lost in a dark and long tunnel

15
00:02:54,220 --> 00:02:55,590
for a long time.

16
00:02:56,600 --> 00:02:58,670
It was so long,
it felt like it was endless.

17
00:02:59,680 --> 00:03:02,270
I thought I would never
be able to get out.

18
00:03:04,610 --> 00:03:05,660
I finally found

19
00:03:07,290 --> 00:03:08,610
the exit.

20
00:03:09,970 --> 00:03:10,940
Finally.

21
00:03:19,829 --> 00:03:20,840
Lee Yeon-seo.

22
00:03:21,410 --> 00:03:23,750
Be my Giselle.

23
00:03:24,890 --> 00:03:26,079
Giselle?

24
00:03:34,740 --> 00:03:37,690
Goodness, you found me.

25
00:03:45,790 --> 00:03:49,180
You wanted to come and roll around
on the sandy beach on your day off?

26
00:03:49,260 --> 00:03:51,290
I was going to stay quiet,

27
00:03:52,870 --> 00:03:54,460
but the guard post was way too old.

28
00:03:54,810 --> 00:03:56,740
Stop smiling. You're annoying me.

29
00:04:00,350 --> 00:04:01,850
What was it like to see me in secret?

30
00:04:01,940 --> 00:04:05,980
I must have looked like a complete fool
to get so easily deceived to dance around.

31
00:04:06,200 --> 00:04:07,080
That was so pretty.

32
00:04:10,870 --> 00:04:12,360
That was really pretty.

33
00:04:13,240 --> 00:04:14,960
This part of my body felt itchy,

34
00:04:15,750 --> 00:04:16,899
and I became sad

35
00:04:17,510 --> 00:04:18,610
and happy.

36
00:04:21,250 --> 00:04:23,850
Don't act like you know
anything about dance.

37
00:04:24,730 --> 00:04:25,830
It's because I don't,

38
00:04:26,750 --> 00:04:28,420
and because there was nothing I could do,

39
00:04:29,000 --> 00:04:30,540
I decided to make this.

40
00:04:30,670 --> 00:04:32,300
I wanted to do something for you,

41
00:04:32,690 --> 00:04:33,880
but as you said,

42
00:04:35,110 --> 00:04:36,520
I don't know anything about ballet.

43
00:04:36,610 --> 00:04:38,020
Then you should just sit still.

44
00:04:38,100 --> 00:04:39,560
Yes, you're useless.

45
00:04:39,640 --> 00:04:41,010
You can't drive. You can't do judo.

46
00:04:41,100 --> 00:04:43,120
And you get on my nerves saying
I'm too mean.

47
00:04:43,210 --> 00:04:44,440
That's enough.

48
00:04:44,750 --> 00:04:46,159
Stop going behind my back.

49
00:04:51,220 --> 00:04:52,180
Should we go now?

50
00:05:02,480 --> 00:05:04,150
Let's go to Fantasia's Night.

51
00:05:04,640 --> 00:05:08,370
Let's show the sponsors
who the prima ballerina is.

52
00:05:09,030 --> 00:05:10,530
What should I prepare?

53
00:05:11,060 --> 00:05:12,380
A revealing dress?

54
00:05:12,470 --> 00:05:13,870
My business smile?

55
00:05:13,960 --> 00:05:14,970
Don't be sarcastic.

56
00:05:15,060 --> 00:05:16,470
You know that this is necessary.

57
00:05:16,560 --> 00:05:19,590
Not all sponsors are perverted or dirty.

58
00:05:19,680 --> 00:05:22,370
It's the dancer's job to attract attention
and bear through it.

59
00:05:22,450 --> 00:05:24,170
Not your job, who only talks.

60
00:05:24,260 --> 00:05:26,810
Over the ten years of my life
as a director, I never made

61
00:05:27,030 --> 00:05:29,410
my ballerinas stand around like flowers,
not even once.

62
00:05:29,490 --> 00:05:30,510
Trust me.

63
00:05:30,770 --> 00:05:31,740
No!

64
00:05:34,600 --> 00:05:35,700
There's a saying,

65
00:05:35,790 --> 00:05:37,850
"There must not be even
a hint of immorality,"

66
00:05:37,940 --> 00:05:39,570
"or of any kind of impurity, or of greed."

67
00:05:39,659 --> 00:05:42,120
Hey, you crook.
What are you talking about?

68
00:05:42,210 --> 00:05:44,409
Don't go. Your dance is more than enough.

69
00:05:44,540 --> 00:05:46,520
There's no reason to prove yourself
any further.

70
00:05:46,740 --> 00:05:49,250
There is no need to bear the wickedness.

71
00:05:49,340 --> 00:05:50,970
Mr. Ji, do you think this is why I...

72
00:05:53,740 --> 00:05:55,409
-Hey.
-You're right.

73
00:05:56,200 --> 00:05:57,610
It could be dirty and uncomfortable.

74
00:05:57,700 --> 00:05:59,280
And it could be worse.

75
00:05:59,370 --> 00:06:01,790
But still, we shouldn't avoid this.
I'll fight with you.

76
00:06:01,880 --> 00:06:04,250
I want to see you become the center of

77
00:06:04,870 --> 00:06:06,010
Fantasia.

78
00:06:10,990 --> 00:06:12,880
I'll manage. Mind your business.

79
00:06:14,290 --> 00:06:15,300
Both of you.

80
00:06:40,250 --> 00:06:42,310
Is this what they call a dream?

81
00:06:48,300 --> 00:06:49,480
My gosh!

82
00:06:51,200 --> 00:06:53,180
How did you know about that beach?

83
00:06:53,270 --> 00:06:54,850
Even I couldn't remember,

84
00:06:55,120 --> 00:06:56,300
so how could you?

85
00:07:02,990 --> 00:07:06,160
You're smiling brightly, aren't you?

86
00:07:06,250 --> 00:07:07,260
You look pretty.

87
00:07:08,270 --> 00:07:09,900
Can you stop saying that?

88
00:07:09,990 --> 00:07:10,870
Are you teasing me?

89
00:07:10,960 --> 00:07:14,480
He said that a useless servant
should do what he can.

90
00:07:15,140 --> 00:07:16,760
I may be useless,

91
00:07:16,850 --> 00:07:18,700
but I will call something pretty if it is.

92
00:07:19,180 --> 00:07:20,460
Because I can do that.

93
00:07:23,230 --> 00:07:24,380
I'm sorry.

94
00:07:30,050 --> 00:07:31,330
You said you didn't like me.

95
00:07:32,080 --> 00:07:33,570
So why are you doing this?

96
00:07:45,630 --> 00:07:46,640
(Mongyu Island, 2005)

97
00:07:46,730 --> 00:07:48,180
(The day I started ballet once again)

98
00:08:14,620 --> 00:08:17,570
(The moment you step into our academy,
you've already acquired your license.)

99
00:08:17,660 --> 00:08:19,110
Your registration has been completed.

100
00:08:19,680 --> 00:08:20,780
Thank you.

101
00:08:23,070 --> 00:08:24,350
Are you Mr. Kim Dan?

102
00:08:25,320 --> 00:08:26,810
-Yes.
-Come over here.

103
00:08:26,900 --> 00:08:28,260
We'll start immediately.

104
00:08:30,200 --> 00:08:31,430
Thank you, sir!

105
00:08:35,789 --> 00:08:36,890
Brakes!

106
00:08:36,970 --> 00:08:38,650
How many times do I need to repeat myself?

107
00:08:38,730 --> 00:08:40,270
First, belt. Second, brakes.

108
00:08:40,360 --> 00:08:41,370
Third.

109
00:08:41,770 --> 00:08:42,960
Third, start the engine!

110
00:08:43,049 --> 00:08:43,970
Again.

111
00:08:44,059 --> 00:08:45,160
Brakes.

112
00:08:46,300 --> 00:08:47,450
Start the engine.

113
00:08:49,910 --> 00:08:52,370
We're pretty much crawling.

114
00:08:54,270 --> 00:08:55,720
That's my report!

115
00:08:55,810 --> 00:08:57,430
Wait! Come on!

116
00:08:57,520 --> 00:08:58,670
(Disqualified.)

117
00:09:01,610 --> 00:09:03,640
-Hu!
-What is it?

118
00:09:03,730 --> 00:09:05,660
Are you seriously keeping an eye on me?

119
00:09:05,750 --> 00:09:06,810
What?

120
00:09:07,160 --> 00:09:09,840
Can't you see that I'm doing my best

121
00:09:09,930 --> 00:09:11,820
to help you drive here?

122
00:09:12,350 --> 00:09:13,580
Why do I sound like this?

123
00:09:13,710 --> 00:09:16,930
I'm trying so hard to help you.

124
00:09:17,010 --> 00:09:18,550
Then you should've told me earlier!

125
00:09:18,640 --> 00:09:21,410
Because of you, I'm disqualified
as soon as I started!

126
00:09:27,570 --> 00:09:30,170
There. Remember the steps and begin.

127
00:09:30,260 --> 00:09:32,810
How could an angel threaten someone
and adopt an expedient?

128
00:09:32,900 --> 00:09:34,000
Begin.

129
00:09:34,700 --> 00:09:36,950
-Fine.
-Are you ready? Begin.

130
00:09:37,030 --> 00:09:39,060
-No!
-Hey, hey!

131
00:09:39,150 --> 00:09:40,640
Do it again.

132
00:09:40,730 --> 00:09:41,870
Which one is the accelerator?

133
00:09:41,960 --> 00:09:43,990
-The right side!
-Here I go.

134
00:09:44,070 --> 00:09:45,920
-Good, good!
-Good, good!

135
00:09:46,010 --> 00:09:48,210
-Which one is the brakes?
-Stop!

136
00:09:48,300 --> 00:09:50,230
How does this work?

137
00:09:53,710 --> 00:09:55,070
Why is it going this way?

138
00:09:57,800 --> 00:10:00,710
Stop! You did it!

139
00:10:02,690 --> 00:10:04,090
No wonder you always cause trouble.

140
00:10:04,180 --> 00:10:05,850
You're not smart to begin with.

141
00:10:07,000 --> 00:10:09,150
I'm never going to learn
anything from you!

142
00:10:10,080 --> 00:10:11,310
You little...

143
00:10:13,600 --> 00:10:14,650
Hey, Dan.

144
00:10:15,710 --> 00:10:16,720
Dan!

145
00:10:17,380 --> 00:10:19,400
You're pretty much a human now.

146
00:10:19,490 --> 00:10:20,550
You're actually angry.

147
00:10:20,640 --> 00:10:22,790
You were too harsh
when I was only a rookie!

148
00:10:22,880 --> 00:10:24,420
-Goodness.
-I didn't know anything.

149
00:10:24,510 --> 00:10:26,000
I didn't know what I was doing.

150
00:10:26,090 --> 00:10:27,980
But you shouted and criticized me!

151
00:10:28,070 --> 00:10:31,020
I wasn't happy with what you were doing,
so I wanted you to snap out of it.

152
00:10:31,110 --> 00:10:32,740
Animals were your only clients.

153
00:10:32,820 --> 00:10:35,380
I was worried you wouldn't know which way

154
00:10:35,460 --> 00:10:38,190
to lead your human client and fail.

155
00:10:38,320 --> 00:10:39,200
What do you mean?

156
00:10:39,290 --> 00:10:41,270
I know this is your first time
dealing with humans.

157
00:10:41,360 --> 00:10:43,030
This is your first time
in a human body too.

158
00:10:43,120 --> 00:10:46,640
But still, don't you think
this was a bit too much?

159
00:10:46,730 --> 00:10:47,610
Listen to this.

160
00:10:47,700 --> 00:10:49,760
"Lee Yeon-seo danced."

161
00:10:49,900 --> 00:10:51,660
"She was beautiful."

162
00:10:52,010 --> 00:10:54,120
"It was the prettiest thing"

163
00:10:54,210 --> 00:10:56,140
"I saw on earth."

164
00:10:56,500 --> 00:10:58,080
(She overworked herself.)

165
00:10:58,650 --> 00:10:59,710
(I was scared)

166
00:11:00,280 --> 00:11:03,100
(that she'd suffer and become unhappy.)

167
00:11:03,710 --> 00:11:07,100
(But when she was dancing,
her face glowed.)

168
00:11:08,160 --> 00:11:09,610
(She was definitely happy.)

169
00:11:10,970 --> 00:11:13,480
How many times did you mention her?

170
00:11:13,570 --> 00:11:14,760
There are 20 lines about her.

171
00:11:14,840 --> 00:11:17,790
At the end, you wrote, "She hugged Rib."

172
00:11:17,880 --> 00:11:19,990
It was just that one sentence.

173
00:11:20,080 --> 00:11:22,100
What kind of report is this?

174
00:11:22,720 --> 00:11:24,220
It's the truth!

175
00:11:24,300 --> 00:11:26,810
Since we're talking about it,
I have a question.

176
00:11:27,160 --> 00:11:28,920
Do you think he's a sturdy one?

177
00:11:29,010 --> 00:11:30,110
What are you saying?

178
00:11:31,520 --> 00:11:32,490
Her life has just begun!

179
00:11:32,580 --> 00:11:34,420
She needs a strong, sturdy rib

180
00:11:34,510 --> 00:11:37,150
beside her for her to become happy.

181
00:11:40,630 --> 00:11:41,680
Could you

182
00:11:42,340 --> 00:11:43,580
look into that for me?

183
00:12:01,970 --> 00:12:04,340
(Choi Seol-hee)

184
00:12:32,410 --> 00:12:33,650
Are you scared?

185
00:12:33,950 --> 00:12:35,450
Well... No.

186
00:12:37,080 --> 00:12:38,490
Because I'll be with you.

187
00:12:59,780 --> 00:13:00,790
It's dangerous.

188
00:13:01,370 --> 00:13:02,470
Stay back.

189
00:13:21,690 --> 00:13:23,810
Listen, Raporas the angel.

190
00:13:24,290 --> 00:13:27,500
You had received a mission
of inspiring artists

191
00:13:27,590 --> 00:13:29,480
so that they would be able to draw things

192
00:13:29,570 --> 00:13:32,340
that would give joy to the deity.

193
00:13:32,610 --> 00:13:34,150
However, you betrayed your mission

194
00:13:34,230 --> 00:13:36,040
and even decided to abandon the deity.

195
00:13:36,170 --> 00:13:38,500
Therefore, you will be judged.

196
00:13:38,590 --> 00:13:40,480
I've fulfilled my mission as an angel.

197
00:13:41,400 --> 00:13:42,500
From now on,

198
00:13:43,870 --> 00:13:46,070
I'd like to become a muse

199
00:13:47,560 --> 00:13:48,800
for one person only.

200
00:14:04,200 --> 00:14:05,740
Becoming an angel,

201
00:14:06,130 --> 00:14:07,630
becoming a human,

202
00:14:08,730 --> 00:14:10,580
starting a life,

203
00:14:11,500 --> 00:14:12,690
and ending a life

204
00:14:14,230 --> 00:14:15,990
all depend on the deity's will.

205
00:14:18,800 --> 00:14:19,820
Don't come.

206
00:14:21,050 --> 00:14:22,280
Don't come. Please.

207
00:14:28,400 --> 00:14:30,020
He is cruel.

208
00:14:30,900 --> 00:14:32,050
Then

209
00:14:32,800 --> 00:14:34,070
why did He give me a heart?

210
00:14:34,640 --> 00:14:35,880
Giving me a heart

211
00:14:35,960 --> 00:14:38,030
and telling me to overcome my feelings

212
00:14:39,310 --> 00:14:41,160
are the doings of a devil!

213
00:14:41,240 --> 00:14:43,930
I will take everything
that the deity has given

214
00:14:44,240 --> 00:14:45,470
away from you.

215
00:15:47,330 --> 00:15:48,210
Please, no...

216
00:15:48,300 --> 00:15:49,310
Please...

217
00:15:49,710 --> 00:15:50,720
Please...

218
00:15:50,810 --> 00:15:51,860
Please...

219
00:15:57,010 --> 00:15:58,070
Please...

220
00:16:49,150 --> 00:16:52,540
(Choi Seol-hee)

221
00:17:01,860 --> 00:17:04,109
(I desperately wanted to become a human,)

222
00:17:05,470 --> 00:17:07,060
(but not in the world)

223
00:17:08,240 --> 00:17:09,260
(where you don't exist.)

224
00:17:50,220 --> 00:17:51,540
(I could neither die)

225
00:17:52,330 --> 00:17:53,960
(nor live a proper life.)

226
00:17:55,460 --> 00:17:56,860
(I was lost for 15 years.)

227
00:18:02,980 --> 00:18:03,990
I think

228
00:18:06,240 --> 00:18:07,780
it will work out really well this time.

229
00:18:09,890 --> 00:18:12,880
You must have lost someone dear to you.

230
00:18:13,630 --> 00:18:16,580
I can still see waves of yearning
in your eyes.

231
00:18:16,660 --> 00:18:18,420
As you prayed with all of your heart,

232
00:18:18,510 --> 00:18:20,270
I am sure your loved one
will be in paradise.

233
00:18:20,360 --> 00:18:23,220
And I can only assume
that she will be in peace.

234
00:18:24,890 --> 00:18:27,840
Does "peace" really exist?

235
00:18:29,160 --> 00:18:30,660
Living is already a torment.

236
00:18:30,830 --> 00:18:32,810
Wishing to be born again
is a silly thought.

237
00:18:32,900 --> 00:18:35,060
And wishing for peace on the other side

238
00:18:36,240 --> 00:18:37,560
sounds lame, doesn't it?

239
00:18:40,640 --> 00:18:41,610
Then,

240
00:18:43,640 --> 00:18:45,660
what is it that you want?

241
00:19:01,940 --> 00:19:03,260
Will you really attend the event?

242
00:19:05,110 --> 00:19:06,950
"If you leave your home,
there will be trouble."

243
00:19:07,040 --> 00:19:07,970
"Stay at home."

244
00:19:08,540 --> 00:19:09,990
That's your horoscope for today.

245
00:19:10,210 --> 00:19:11,350
Doesn't this sound too eerie?

246
00:19:11,440 --> 00:19:13,250
One of you recited some sayings to me.

247
00:19:13,470 --> 00:19:14,790
And you are reading my horoscope?

248
00:19:14,870 --> 00:19:16,500
It's because we don't feel good
about this.

249
00:19:16,590 --> 00:19:17,510
Horoscopes are big data

250
00:19:17,600 --> 00:19:20,330
that contain the principles
of the universe and human history.

251
00:19:20,420 --> 00:19:21,430
You shouldn't ignore it.

252
00:19:21,520 --> 00:19:23,810
I'll face it.

253
00:19:23,890 --> 00:19:25,920
I probably can't avoid it
even if I want to.

254
00:19:30,010 --> 00:19:31,020
Fine.

255
00:19:31,420 --> 00:19:32,560
Since you're attending it,

256
00:19:32,650 --> 00:19:35,420
go announce it with a bright smile.

257
00:19:35,550 --> 00:19:36,610
"Fantasia belongs to me."

258
00:19:36,700 --> 00:19:38,680
"This job is mine." Make it official.

259
00:19:39,690 --> 00:19:40,920
I'll be out after I get changed.

260
00:19:42,460 --> 00:19:43,470
Okay.

261
00:20:00,900 --> 00:20:02,000
Do you like me?

262
00:20:02,390 --> 00:20:04,020
Just say yes or no.

263
00:20:06,180 --> 00:20:07,280
Did you like me?

264
00:20:09,480 --> 00:20:11,680
Do you?

265
00:20:15,770 --> 00:20:16,740
No.

266
00:20:28,480 --> 00:20:30,160
Hello. What would you like?

267
00:20:30,240 --> 00:20:32,220
Something to help me be okay on my own.

268
00:20:32,310 --> 00:20:33,540
-Pardon?
-Relaxing pills,

269
00:20:33,630 --> 00:20:35,220
sedatives, or stimulant drugs.

270
00:20:35,790 --> 00:20:37,110
I don't care what it is.

271
00:20:38,160 --> 00:20:39,180
I've been

272
00:20:40,060 --> 00:20:41,770
relying on people too much.

273
00:20:43,000 --> 00:20:45,640
I've been relying on a guy
who doesn't even like me.

274
00:20:46,570 --> 00:20:49,210
I'm not the type of person
who easily gets attached.

275
00:20:51,760 --> 00:20:53,700
I must have lost my mind
for a second or something.

